    <h2>Paragraphs</h2>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-7">
   <div class="small-12 columns">
    <p>By default, subsequent paragraphs have a margin bottom of <code>1 rem</code> and the last-child has no margin. That way, if a single paragraph is used, it will always have inherit the bottom margin of it's parent.</p>
   </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="example">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="small-6 columns">
        <h4>A column header</h4>
        <p>Bender, hurry! This fuel's expensive! Also, <strong>we're dying!</strong> This opera's as lousy as it is brilliant! Your lyrics lack subtlety. You can't just have your characters announce how they feel. That makes me feel angry! Why did I take a cab? Are you crazy?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="small-6 columns">
        <h4>Another column</h4>
        <p>I meant 'physically'. Look, perhaps you could let me work for food? I could clean the floors or paint a fence? Daddy Bender, we're hungry. I feel like I was mauled by Jesus. I'm sorry, guys. <strong>I never meant</strong> to hurt you. Just to destroy everything you ever believed in.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <pre>
    <code><%= display_code('
<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-6 columns">
    <h4>A column header</h4>
    <p>Bender, hurry! This fuels...</p>
  </div>

  <div class="small-6 columns">
    <h4>Another column</h4>
    <p>I meant physically...</p>
  </div>
</div>') %></code>
  </pre>
</div>


